&lt;p&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;Texas Chiller Systems&lt;/strong&gt;, we take pride in serving our customers with excellence and supporting our employees with the same care and attention. Headquartered in San Antonio, we were built on a foundation of strong values that guide how we work, lead, and serve, always putting people first and striving to exceed expectations for our team and our customers in every interaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;444&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Journeyman HVAC Service Mechanic&lt;/strong&gt; serves as a key technical resource for fellow service mechanics, providing technical support, guidance, and training while ensuring the reliable operation of HVAC systems through inspections, testing, repairs, and preventive maintenance. This role is essential to maintaining the comfort, safety, and performance of the environments we service while helping elevate the technical capability of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties/Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates strong attention to detail and advanced diagnostic skills related to HVAC system performance. Experience with a wide range of systems, from split systems to chillers, ensures optimal system operation and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates work processes effectively, particularly on large projects. Provides on-site leadership by managing both overall project objectives and detailed execution to support successful completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilizes hand tools, power tools, gauges, and measuring equipment with precision and expertise for troubleshooting and planned maintenance activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds and maintains strong customer relationships by clearly explaining completed work and ensuring customer confidence and satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains clear communication and thorough documentation to ensure all project stakeholders remain informed and aligned throughout project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serves as a technical resource to others by offering support, guiding technicians, and coordinating multi-technician service calls to promote team growth and success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participates in on-call stand-by rotation and effectively manages multiple tasks while maintaining composure under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adheres to safety standards both on the road and on job sites. Maintains tools, service vehicle, and inventory in an organized and ready state.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages material purchasing and service vehicle stock efficiently to streamline processes and maintain smooth operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Encouraged to be in good standing with local union 211and/or willing to join&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HVAC Unitary Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Split systems – all brands up to 120 tons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mini-split systems – up to 3-ton heat pump and all brands MultiZone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;VRV Heat Pump and VRV Heat Recovery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rooftop units (RTU) – all brands up to 150+ tons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Water source heat pumps – all brands up to 120 tons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-contained systems – water-cooled and air-cooled with remote condenser&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CRAC units – Liebert/Data Aire/Stulz&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HVAC Airside Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fan Powered Boxes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;VAV Boxes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;VFD theory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Air Handler – theory of AHU operation and control valve operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhaust fans – centrifugal upblast roof fans, centrifugal inline fans, and vane axial high-pressure fans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pumps and Piping Systems Skills:&lt;/strong&g

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Texas Chiller Systems (TCS) we focus on excellence and teamwork across HVAC, plumbing, and electrical trades. We support commercial properties with strong maintenance, repair, and installation services. The Account Executive - Outside sales is the face of Texas Chiller Systems who develops, expands, and protects long-term customer relationships across commercial, industrial, institutional, and mission-critical environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role blends&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;strategic hunting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;, relationship-driven consulting,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;technical solutioning&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;across HVAC service, retrofit, and small-to-mid-size project opportunities. Your mission: grow profitable owner-direct business, deepen existing accounts, and elevate TCS’s reputation for reliability and excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive new owner-direct business development through prospecting, territory mapping, and consistent outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong customer relationships with building owners, facility managers, property teams, and industrial operators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow a personal book of business, focusing on renewals, expansion, and customer retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct site visits, assessments, and discovery to identify service, maintenance, and retrofit needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop scopes and collaborate with Operations/Estimating to ensure accurate pricing and feasibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and deliver compelling proposals for maintenance agreements, equipment replacements, upgrades, and retrofit projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain disciplined CRM usage including activity tracking, forecasting, deal probability, and pipeline updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up on technician-identified service opportunities and ensure timely engagement with customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Service, Project Management, Estimating, and Purchasing to ensure seamless execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay active in the market through industry events, networking, and competitive research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–7+ years of successful outside B2B sales experience in commercial HVAC, mechanical services, building services, or related technical industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales quotas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong relationship-building and consultative selling skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand mechanical systems and translate technical concepts into value-focused business conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High discipline in CRM usage, pipeline management, and forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, negotiation, and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver’s license and willingness to travel within territory and between TCS branch locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work here:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-Growth Market Opportunity - Texas is booming, and TCS is expanding aggressively with enormous untapped owner-direct potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Technical Backbone - You’ll sell with confidence knowing you have deep bench strength in Service, Projects, Estimating, and field expertise that consistently delivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Compensation Structure - A strong base + incentive model tied directly to profitable growth. Uncapped commissions equal unlimited earning potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomy with Support - You’ll run your market with independence while having true operational alignment behind you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Culture That Values Relationships - Internally and externall

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preventative Maintenance Coordinator &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Preventative Maintenance Coordinator is responsible for coordinating and managing preventative maintenance agreements (PMAs) for HVAC mechanical customers across assigned markets. This role serves as the primary point of contact for PMA coordination, customer communication, scheduling oversight, and renewal support while partnering closely with Account Managers, Dispatch, Service Operations, CSRs, and local field teams. This is an individual contributor role focused on delivering a high level of customer service, ensuring contracted maintenance obligations are fulfilled, and supporting operational efficiency across service markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend turnover meetings for newly awarded preventative maintenance agreements and ensure successful PMA setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review contracted maintenance hours monthly and coordinate scheduling with local markets to ensure contract compliance and workload alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Dispatch and local service teams to schedule technicians for preventative maintenance visits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm all required tools, materials, and parts are identified and coordinated with local CSR teams to support proper dispatching and job readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate regularly with customers to ensure preventative maintenance expectations and service needs are being met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Account Managers to support customer satisfaction, relationship management, and service continuity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate turnover documentation and communicate all PMA details to internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with customers and internal teams regarding PMA renewals and continuation of service agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with Service Operations to ensure required parts are ordered and available for scheduled maintenance visits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor PMA completion status and follow up on outstanding service items, deficiencies, or customer concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuous improvement efforts related to preventative maintenance scheduling, communication, and operational execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records, scheduling data, and customer communications within company systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete required testing documentation and provide reports to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent required; associate degree or technical training preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in HVAC mechanical service, preventative maintenance coordination, dispatching, or service operations preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of preventative maintenance agreements and service scheduling processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to coordinate multiple projects, schedules, and priorities across various markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer service and relationship management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and organizational skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work cross-functionally with account Managers, dispatch, service Teams, and operations leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office and service management software platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of HVAC systems, service workflows, and field operations preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of COINS ERP systems preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer Focus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication&lt;/li&gt;
